The paper deals with quantum communication complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves Fourier analysis, which is a common tool in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the Log-rank Conjecture, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) related to communication complexity. Finally, the paper presents results on the bounded-error and exact quantum communication complexity of XOR functions, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and quantum computing (cs.QU).
